    • Field Detail

      • scales

        protected int[] scales
        The PDF was created using the scaled axes. scales holds the scale factors for that and they can be used on variables in the original reference frame (= not scaled) to transform to the reference frame of the PDF. They are each "1" by default. The first dimension is for the x axis and the 2nd is for the y axis.

      • bckGndSep

        protected float[] bckGndSep
        The x separation and y separation in the original reference frame that are used to define the critical separation for association of 2 points 
             it's relationship to this.threeS[1] is:
         xd = (bckGndSep[0]/scales[0])
         xd *= xd;
         yd = (bckGndSep[1]/scales[1])
         yd *= yd;
         
         this.threeS[1] should == sqrt(xd + yd)

      • threeS

        protected float[] threeS
        These are the 3 discrete points of the x-points of the PDF between which continuous lines are interpreted. The three points are: threeS[0] is 0; threeS[1] is the representative background separation point. The threshold factor should be multiplied by it upon use. threeS[2] is a separation value larger than threeS[1] and is the last with a count or density above approximately 0. The threshold factor should be multiplied by it upon use.

      • threeSCounts

        protected float[] threeSCounts
        These are the normalized counts of the 3 discrete points in threeS. They are the y-points of the PDF between which continuous lines are interpreted.

      • threeSErrors

        protected float[] threeSErrors
        the errors for the points in (threeSs, threeSCounts)
